1	Use Case [#]:  [Reschedule an Appointment]

1.1	Description
The Customer decides to reschedule their appointment.

1.2	Level
High-Level Summary

1.3	Trigger
The Customer decides to edit/change their booking.

1.4	Primary Actor
Customer

1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
Business Admin

1.6	Stakeholders 
Employees (whoever was going to perform the service)
Other Customers

1.7	Preconditions
The customer should already have a booking in place.

1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Customer chooses existing booking.
2.	Customer edits the date or service.
3.	Customer submits new booking request
  Execute: Proccess Appointments.
5. Booking is rescheduled

1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: Date/Time slots are unavailable:
1.	Application displays a warning message to tryagain later
2.	The appointment remains on schedule.

1.	Alternative: Customers chooses reschedule at a later date.
1.	System cancels currently booked appointment.
2.	Voucher code is sent to the customer
3.	Booking is removed from scheduled appointments for both business admin and customer.

1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition

The customer receives confirmation of new date/time. 
Applicable fees are charged. 

1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
The booking will remain on schedule if failure occurs

1.10.3	Failure End Condition
The customer cannot change the appointment and the appointment remains unchanged.

1.11	Frequency
Unknown

1.12	Special Requirements
1.12.1	Performance
Customer must get available date/time displayed to them within 3 seconds
Proccessing of the request should take a minimum of 24hrs
1.12.2	Security
1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Customer should just be able to click a button to reschedule and shown the available time they can pick from.
Once they submit the new request they should wait for and receive an email confirming the new details.

1.12.4	Other
1.13	Issues and Next Steps
Customer cannot change the service of the appointment only the date and time 
